  "buggy_functions": [
    "ata_device_blacklist"
  ],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The Samsung SSD 860 EVO device is missing from the ata_device_blacklist table. Samsung SSD 840 and 850 models already have entries (lines 4562-4565) with ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag to disable queued TRIM support due to known issues. Without this entry, Samsung 860 EVO attempts to use queued TRIM commands which causes timeouts and lockups (as described by the 'SEND FPDMA QUEUED' error in the bug report). The fix requires adding a similar blacklist entry for Samsung SSD 860* models with the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag. This horkage flag is checked in ata_dev_configure_ncq_send_recv() at line 2218, where it disables queued TRIM support by clearing the DSM_TRIM bit from the NCQ Send/Recv commands when the flag is set."
}

